3) In the main function `mineWoodLogs`, initialize a variable `logsNeeded = 4`.
4) While `logsNeeded > 0`:
   a) Use `exploreUntil` with a random direction, maxTime 60, and a callback that finds any log block within 32 blocks using `bot.findBlock` with a matching function `isLogBlock`.
   b) If a log block is found, call `mineBlock(bot, block.name, logsNeeded)` to mine the remaining needed logs. Update `logsNeeded` by subtracting the number of logs actually collected (we can check inventory after mining).
   c) If no log block is found, break the loop.
5) After the loop, if `logsNeeded > 0`, chat that not enough logs were found.

